=Heinrich von Kleist (1777-1811)=
==Life==
* 1777 born in Frankfurt an der Oder
==Persons==
* Ernst von Pfuel
* Henriette Vogel
* Charlotte Margarete von Zenge
==Literature==
===PhD Dissertations===
* Thomas Paul Quinn: Heinrich von Kleist und die Frage nach Gott, University of California, Berkeley, 1985
* Theo Honnef: Heinrich von Kleist in der Literatur der DDR, The University of North Carolina, 1986
* Margarete Johanna Landwehr: Heinrich von Kleist and the reader enigmas and ambiguities in his prose works, Harvard University, 1986
* Sabine Go: Fame and egocentricity in Kleist's Prinz Friedrich von Homburg a look at the darker side of humanity, Queen's University at Kingston, 1986
* Silvia Vogt: Studien zum Liebestod-Motiv in den Erzählungen Heinrich von Kleists, The University of Manitoba, 1987
* Steven R. Huff: Starres Leben: The problem of passivity in the works of Heinrich von Kleist, Princeton University, 1987
* Edda Sonnhilde Brunner: Sprache, Ideologie und Praxis in Kleists "Marquise von O....": Spannungsmomente und gesellschaftliche Machtverhaeltnisse, University of California, Berkeley, 1990
* Christina Eiko Günther: Sexual and textual politics reconsidered: Heinrich von Kleist's "Amphitryon" and "Marquise von O." vs. their adaptations in the 1960s, he University of Wisconsin-Madison, 1990
* Heather Diane Pitts: Roleplaying and strategic interaction in Heinrich von Kleist's later dramas, Queen's University at Kingston, 1991
* Bianca Theisen: Gottes Griffel: Simulationen des Heiligen bei Heinrich von Kleist, Stanford University, 1992
* Erika Berroth: Amphibien und grüne Glaeser: Überlegungen zu Geschlecht und Erkenntnis bei Heinrich von Kleist, University of California, Santa Barbara, 1993
* Nancy Nobile: Allegorical education: Pedagogical writings of Heinrich von Kleist, The Johns Hopkins University, 1994
* Andreas Gailus: Ruling exceptions: Heinrich von Kleist and the emergence of the modern German novella, Columbia University, 1996
* Renee M. Schell: The power to look: Gender and identity politics in selected works of Heinrich von Kleist, Stanford University, 1997
* Claudia Beatrice Svoboda: Narrative Illusion: Textual Ambiguity and Problems of Seeing in Four Novellas of Heinrich von Kleist, Harvard University, 1997
* Matthew Pollard: The Bodies of Kleist: Aspects of Corporeality in his Dramatic Works, McGill University, 1997
* Grant Profant McAllister: Kleist's female title characters as aesthetic disruption of idealist discourse, The University of Utah, 2001
* Christiane K. Eydt-Beebe: Reception and translations: Heinrich von Kleist's Der zerbrochne Krug in english translations, The Pennsylvania State University, 2002
===Monographs===
* Herbert Kraft: Kleist: Leben und Werk, Münster: Aschendorff Verlag, 2007
===Articles===
* Karl-Heinz Meurer: "Gerechtigkeit zwischen Differenz und Identität in Heinrich von Kleists Michael Kohlhaas", Deutsche Vierteljahrsschrift für Literaturwissenschaft und Geistesgeschichte, Volume 75, 2001, pp. 123-144